<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>



<p>At Clínic Sanlez, we value the privacy of our clients and are committed to protecting any personal information you provide to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your data when you engage with our services, whether online or at our clinic.</p>
<p>We collect personal information such as your name, contact details (including phone number and email), address, and pet-related data, like your pet's name, species, breed, and medical history. This information is gathered to provide you with the best possible veterinary care, manage appointments, and communicate effectively with you regarding your pet’s health.</p>
<p>In some cases, we may also collect payment details to process transactions for services rendered. When visiting our website, we may automatically gather information like your IP address and browsing activity to improve our online services and provide a better user experience.</p>
<p>We use the information collected for several purposes, including scheduling appointments, sending reminders about upcoming visits, processing payments, and ensuring the care of your pet is documented accurately. We may also use your contact details to notify you of important updates, such as changes in clinic hours or health advisories.</p>
<p>Your personal information is kept secure using industry-standard practices. We limit access to your data to authorized personnel and use encryption and other security measures to protect it from unauthorized access. We do not share your information with third parties unless required by law or when necessary to fulfill our services, such as processing payments.</p>
<p>As a client, you have the right to access the information we have about you, correct or update any details, and request that we delete your personal data when it is no longer necessary for our services. You can also opt out of receiving non-essential communications from us, such as newsletters or promotional messages.</p>
<p>Our website may use cookies to improve your experience and provide personalized content. You have the option to disable cookies through your browser settings if you prefer, but this may affect how certain features of the website function.</p>
<p>We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy as necessary to reflect changes in our practices or comply with legal obligations. We encourage you to check this page periodically to stay informed about how we protect your privacy.</p>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns about how your data is handled, please contact us at Clínic Sanlez, and we will be happy to assist you.</p>
